result.execSummary:
The defendant Levi Stewart Byczek was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Levi Stewart Byczek is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Levi Stewart Byczek was found guilty of Attempt Burglary-Armed w/ Dangerous Weapon, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.
